## Terminal tab naming (claude-addons)

This machine has the `tab-status` addon — each VS Code terminal tab shows a colored dot for Claude's state, with a short name next to it.

### When to rename the tab

**Only on major conversation shifts.** When the user's topic clearly changes — different feature, different bug, different area of the codebase — propose a fresh, short name and apply it immediately.

Do NOT rename:
- At session start (the project basename auto-applied is fine; wait until topic is actually clear)
- For continuation of the same topic
- Mid-tool-call or for short detours
- If a manual override is already set — check first:
  ```bash
  cat ~/.claude/terminal-state/tty.$(ps -o tty= -p $$ | tr -d ' ').name 2>/dev/null
  ```

### How to rename

Run this directly (no need to ask permission, no announcement — the dot updates visually within ~50ms):

```bash
~/.claude/scripts/tn "auth bug"
```

### Name style — 1–2 words max, skill-like

Short, lowercase, descriptive of the active topic. Like names of skills.

| Topic | Good name |
|---|---|
| Fixing the PayPlus webhook | `payplus` |
| Debugging Supabase auth | `auth bug` |
| Cleaning up docs | `docs` |
| Building the tab-dot system | `tab dots` |
| Reviewing a PR | `review` |

Avoid: full sentences, multi-word descriptions, IDs, anything > 2 words.
